quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,93,"All food was lawful to the Children of Israel save what Israel forbade for himself before the Torah was sent down. Say: 'Bring you the Torah now, and recite it, if you are truthful"
  3,94,"Whoso forges falsehood against God after that, those are the evildoers"
  3,95,"Say: 'God has spoken the truth; therefore follow the creed of Abraham, a man of pure faith and no idolater"
  3,96,"The first House established for the people was that at Bekka, a place holy, and a guidance to all beings"
  3,97,"Therein are clear signs -- the station of Abraham, and whosoever enters it is in security. It is the duty of all men towards God to come to the House a pilgrim, if he is able to make his way there. As for the unbeliever, God is All-sufficient nor needs any being"
  3,98,"Say: 'People of the Book, why do you disbelieve in the signs of God? Surely God is witness of the things you do"
  3,99,"Say: 'People of the Book, why do you bar from God's way the believer, desiring to make it crooked, yourselves being witnesses? God is not heedless of the things you do"
  3,100,"O believers, if you obey a sect of those who have been given the Book, they will turn you, after you have believed, into unbelievers"
  3,101,"How can you disbelieve, seeing you have God's signs recited to you, and His Messenger among you? Whosoever holds fast to God, he is guided to a straight path"
  3,102,"O believers, fear God as He should be feared, and see you do not die, save in surrender"
  3,103,"And hold you fast to God's bond, together, and do not scatter; remember God's blessing upon you when you were enemies, and He brought your hearts together, so that by His blessing you became brothers. You were upon the brink of a pit of Fire, and He delivered you from it; even so God makes clear to you His signs; so haply you will be guided"
  3,104,"Let there be one nation of you, calling to good, and bidding to honour, and forbidding dishonour; those are the prosperers"
  3,105,Be not as those who scattered and fell into variance after the clear signs came to them; those there awaits a mighty chastisement
  3,106,"the day when some faces are blackened, and some faces whitened. As for those whose faces are blackened -- 'Did you disbelieve after you had believed? Then taste the chastisement for that you disbelieved"
  3,107,"But as for those whose faces are whitened, they shall be in God's mercy, therein dwelling forever"
  3,108,"These are the signs of God We recite to thee in truth, and God desires not any injustice to living beings"
  3,109,"To God belongs all that is in the heavens and in the earth, and unto Him all matters are returned"
  3,110,"You are the best nation ever brought forth to men, bidding to honour, and forbidding dishonour, and believing in God. Had the People of the Book believed, it were better for them; some of them are believers, but the most of them are ungodly"
  3,111,"They will not harm you, except a little hurt; and if they fight with you, they will turn on you their backs; then they will not be helped"
  3,112,"Abasement shall be pitched on them, wherever they are come upon, except they be in a bond of God, and a bond of the people; they will be laden with the burden of God's anger, and poverty shall be pitched on them; that, because they disbelieved in God's signs, and slew the Prophets without right; that, for that they acted rebelliously and were transgressors"